          <p>Two reasons. Either the results are not visible — they cannot see what they are paying for. Or there is no relationship — they feel like a transaction, not a client. Both are delivery failures, not sales failures.</p>
          <div class="tr-read-section" style="margin-top:12px;">The monthly report is the product</div>
          <p>The work is the GMB management. The product is the report. A client who receives a clear report showing profile views up 23%, calls up 8 this month, and 4 new reviews added does not cancel. A client who never hears from you and does not know what they are paying for does cancel. Send the report every single month.</p>
          <div class="tr-read-section" style="margin-top:12px;">Handling "I want to pause"</div>
          <p>"I want to pause" almost always means "I cannot currently see the value." The correct response is not to reduce the price — it is to open the report and walk through it with them. If there is no visible progress, the problem is delivery not price. Fix the delivery. If the results are genuinely there, show them. "Your calls from Google were up 12 last month — the question is whether you want to keep that going."</p>
