<!-- ─── OUTREACH ─── -->
<!-- ─── NO SHOW ─── -->
<div id="sc-booking" class="tp active">
<div class="card">
<div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128222;</div><div><div class="ct">No Show — Rebook</div><div class="cs">They had a call booked and didn't pick up. Don't chase. Just reopen the door.</div></div></div>
<div class="ibox"><p>They didn't answer. That's fine — they're on the tools. Send once at 48 hours. If still no reply, add them to the Follow-Up tab with a 4-week date and move on. Don't chase more than twice total.</p></div>
<div class="csec">48 hours after the missed call</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Second message — last attempt before long-term nurture</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">hey [Name], just circling back — i still have your google profile pulled up from when we were supposed to speak. happy to find another slot whenever works for you. otherwise no problem at all.</div></div>
<div class="csec">If they reply and want to rebook</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Rebook confirmation</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">perfect — locked in for [day] at [time]. i'll call you on this number. speak then.</div></div>
<div class="wbox"><p>After two attempts with no reply — don't send a third. Add them to the <strong>Follow-Up</strong> tab with a 4-week date. They were warm enough to book once. They may come back.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!-- /no-show -->

<!-- ─── AUDIT ─── -->
<div id="sc-audit" class="tp">
<div class="card">
<div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128269;</div><div><div class="ct">Pre-Call Prep Checklist</div><div class="cs">Do this before you dial — the call runs on its own when you are properly prepared</div></div></div>
<div class="ibox"><p>The audit is a phone call. You already know what is wrong before you dial. You are walking them through what you found — not discovering it live. Tick these off, then go to On The Call for the exact words to use.</p></div>
<div class="csec">Before you call — tick these off</div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Open Audit Tool → fill in their name, trade, location</label></div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Search their business on Google Maps — have it open on screen</label></div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Work through the GMB checklist — tick what is there, note what is missing</label></div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Search "[trade] in [location]" incognito — are they in the 3-pack or not showing at all?</label></div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Note the review count of the top 1–2 competitors ranking above them</label></div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Open their website on your phone — speed, mobile layout, click-to-call, clear CTA</label></div>
<div class="chi"><input type="checkbox" onchange="chkT(this)"><label>Have 3 specific findings ready — lead with these on the call</label></div>
<div style="margin-top:16px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--navy),var(--nl));border-radius:11px;padding:16px 20px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
  <div>
    <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;margin-bottom:3px;">Ready to call?</div>
    <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);">Switch to On The Call for stage-by-stage scripts</div>
  </div>
  <button onclick="showTab('sc','oncall',document.querySelector('[onclick*=oncall]'))" style="background:var(--blue);color:#fff;border:none;padding:9px 18px;border-radius:8px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer;font-family:var(--fh);white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">On The Call &#128241; &rarr;</button>
</div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128241;</div><div><div class="ct">On The Call — Walk-Through Order</div><div class="cs">This is a phone call. You are their guide. They don't share a screen — you describe what you are seeing.</div></div></div>
<div class="csec">Opening the call</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Call opener — say this immediately</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">Right [Name], I have got your Google profile up on my screen — I am going to walk you through exactly what I found. Some of it is fine, some of it is costing you calls. I will just go through it and you can stop me if anything doesn't make sense. Sound good?</div></div>
<div class="csec">Walking through the findings</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">For each finding — say this pattern</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">So the first thing I can see is [finding]. What that means for you is [consequence — e.g. "Google is showing you less often because..."] — and the fix is actually straightforward, it's just [what to do].</div></div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Showing them the competition</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">The businesses showing up above you right now — the top one has [X] reviews and a fully built-out profile. That's why they get the call when someone searches [trade] in [area]. It's not that they do better work. Their profile just looks more complete to Google.</div></div>
<div class="csec">The soft mention</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">After going through the findings — plant the seed</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">Look — our guys could take all of this off your plate. But honestly, you're completely fine to do it yourself, and this call gives you everything you need to get started. Most people do exactly that at first. It only becomes a conversation when it starts feeling like a burden to keep on top of alongside running the business.</div></div>
<div class="csec">The one question</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Ask this once, then stop talking</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">Based on what we have looked at today — do you want us to handle this for you?</div></div>
<div class="wbox"><p><strong>Then stop talking.</strong> Whoever speaks next, speaks next. Do not fill the silence. The call is over when they answer — your job is to wait for the answer.</p></div>
<div class="csec">Exit scripts</div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If Yes</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">Brilliant. I will send the details over today. Once you are happy with everything I will get everything moving — the GMB will be sorted within 48 hours. Any questions before I send that over?</div></div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If Maybe / Need to think — set the 2-week follow-up</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">completely fine. i will send you the action list now — the fix once stuff and the weekly habits. have a go at it yourself and i'll call you in two weeks. by then you will either have it sorted and you won't need us, or you'll have a better sense of how much time it actually takes to keep on top of alongside running the business. either way you'll know where you stand. does that work?</div></div>
<div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If No / Not yet</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
<div class="st">No problem at all. I will send you a summary — the action list is yours to use whether we work together or not. Good luck with it.</div></div>
<div class="ibox"><p style="font-size:12.5px;">After every call — yes, maybe, or no — go to <strong>Send-Out</strong> in the nav and generate their playbook within 30 minutes. This is the most important thing you do after hanging up.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="card"><div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128737;</div><div><div class="ct">On-Call Objections</div></div></div>
<div class="ob"><div class="oh" onclick="togO(this)">"What does it cost?" (mid-call) <span class="oa">&#9660;</span></div><div class="obody">Let me just show you the last couple of things first so the recommendation makes sense — then I will walk you through the options. Two more minutes.<div class="onote">Delay price until after the findings. The audit justifies the fee.</div></div></div>
<div class="ob"><div class="oh" onclick="togO(this)">"It is too expensive" <span class="oa">&#9660;</span></div><div class="obody">completely understand. a well-run GMB brings in 5 to 15 extra jobs a month. at £200 average that is £1,000 to £3,000 extra. we charge £147 a month to manage the thing that generates that. does the value make sense when you look at it that way?<div class="onote">ROI frame. Ask if it makes sense. Stop.</div></div></div>
<div class="ob"><div class="oh" onclick="togO(this)">"I need to think about it" <span class="oa">&#9660;</span></div><div class="obody">of course — can I ask what specifically you want to think through? I would rather address it now while we are talking than have you go away with a question I could have answered.<div class="onote">Get the real objection. Don't let it float.</div></div></div>
<div class="ob"><div class="oh" onclick="togO(this)">"I need to speak to my partner" <span class="oa">&#9660;</span></div><div class="obody">absolutely — when do you expect to speak to them? I will send you a summary of everything we looked at so you go into that conversation with something concrete.<div class="onote">Get a date. Send the send-out immediately.</div></div></div>
</div>
<div class="card"><div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#129302;</div><div><div class="ct">Reply Generator</div></div></div>
<div style="margin-bottom:12px;"><label class="fl">What did they say after the call?</label><textarea class="fi" id="rg-zoom-input" placeholder="Paste their reply..." style="min-height:65px;"></textarea></div>
<button class="btn btnp" onclick="generateReply('zoom')" style="width:100%;margin-bottom:12px;">Generate Reply Options</button>
<div id="rg-zoom-out" style="display:none;"></div>
</div>
</div><!-- /audit -->

<!-- ─── ON THE CALL ─── -->
<div id="sc-oncall" class="tp">
<div class="card">
<div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128241;</div><div><div class="ct">On The Call — Full Five-Stage Flow</div><div class="cs">Phone call. You have done the prep. Now walk them through what you found.</div></div></div>
<div class="ibox"><p>This is not a pitch and it is not a Zoom. It is a phone call where you walk them through their own profile. You already know what is wrong. Your job is to make sure they understand what it means for their business — then ask the one question.</p></div>
<div class="call-stages">
  <button class="call-stage-btn active" onclick="showCallStage('discovery',this)">1 · Discovery</button>
  <button class="call-stage-btn" onclick="showCallStage('frame',this)">2 · Frame</button>
  <button class="call-stage-btn" onclick="showCallStage('auditwalk',this)">3 · Walk-Through</button>
  <button class="call-stage-btn" onclick="showCallStage('softmention',this)">4 · Soft Mention</button>
  <button class="call-stage-btn" onclick="showCallStage('exit',this)">5 · Exit</button>
</div>
<div class="call-stage-panel active" id="cs-discovery">
  <div class="cnote" style="margin-bottom:16px;"><strong>Stage 1 — Discovery (2–3 questions max)</strong>Before you walk through the audit, ask a couple of questions. This builds context so your findings land in the right frame. Listen properly — reference what they tell you when you get to Stage 3.</div>
  <div class="csec">Pick 2–3 — click to copy</div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"How are you getting most of your leads at the moment?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"How long have you had the Google profile set up?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"Have you noticed competitors coming up above you when you search your trade in your area?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"What does a good month look like for you in terms of enquiries?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"Is there a particular type of job or area you would love more of?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"Have you tried anything on the marketing side before?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="disc-q" onclick="copyDiscQ(this)"><span class="disc-q-txt">"What made you agree to this call — was there something that stood out?"</span><button class="disc-q-copy">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="wbox" style="margin-top:12px;"><p><strong>Listen for:</strong> word of mouth reliance, slow months, frustration with previous agencies. Reference it in Stage 3: "You mentioned you want more bathroom installs — this is exactly why you are not getting them from Google right now..."</p></div>
</div>
<div class="call-stage-panel" id="cs-frame">
  <div class="cnote" style="margin-bottom:16px;"><strong>Stage 2 — Frame (one sentence, then start)</strong>Set the tone before you walk through anything. Removes any sales anxiety before the findings land.</div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Frame — say this once, then start walking</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">Right — I have got your Google profile up on my screen. I am going to walk you through exactly what I found, good and bad. It is not a pitch — it is just what is there. You will know exactly where you stand by the end of it. Sound good?</div></div>
</div>
<div class="call-stage-panel" id="cs-auditwalk">
  <div class="cnote" style="margin-bottom:16px;"><strong>Stage 3 — Walk-Through (go in order)</strong>You are describing what you see. They are picturing it. Go slowly. Pause after each finding. Don't fill the silence — let it land.</div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">Walk-through — describe what you see on their profile</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">1. "So right now, when someone searches [trade] in [area]..."
2. Tell them where they appear — 3-pack, page one, or not at all
3. First finding: "The first thing I can see is [finding]. What that means is [consequence]."
4. Pause. Let it land. If they say "oh really?" — good. Don't rush to the next one.
5. Second finding: same pattern — finding, consequence, pause.
6. Third finding: same.
7. "The businesses ranking above you — the top one has [X] reviews. Not better work. Just a better-looking profile to Google."
8. Pause. Let the comparison land.</div></div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If they ask how to fix something mid-walk</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">I'll go through exactly what to do at the end — I want to make sure you have the full picture first. Two more minutes.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="call-stage-panel" id="cs-softmention">
  <div class="cnote" style="margin-bottom:16px;"><strong>Stage 4 — Soft Mention (plant the seed, not the pitch)</strong>After the walk-through. Don't close hard. Say this naturally — like you're giving them the option, not selling them on it.</div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">The soft mention — say this once, naturally</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">Look — our guys could take all of this off your plate. But honestly, you're completely fine to do it yourself, and this call gives you everything you need to get started. Most people do exactly that at first. It only becomes a conversation when it starts feeling like a burden alongside running the business.</div></div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If they ask about cost before you've asked the question</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">Let me just go through the last bit and then I will walk you through the options — makes more sense once you have the full picture. Two more minutes.</div></div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">The one question — ask this once</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">Based on what we have looked at today — do you want us to handle this for you?</div></div>
  <div class="wbox"><p><strong>Then stop talking.</strong> The next person who speaks, speaks. Do not fill the gap. This is the most important moment of the call.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="call-stage-panel" id="cs-exit">
  <div class="cnote" style="margin-bottom:16px;"><strong>Stage 5 — Exit (always leave with a next step)</strong>Whatever their answer — give them something concrete before you hang up. No open-ended endings.</div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If Yes</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">Brilliant. I will send the details over today — just confirm you are happy with everything and I will get things moving. The GMB will be sorted within 48 hours. Any questions before I send that?</div></div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If Maybe / Thinking about it — set a 2-week follow-up</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">completely fine. i will send you the action list now — the fix once stuff and the weekly habits. have a go at it yourself and i'll call you in two weeks. by then you will either have it sorted and you won't need us, or you'll have a better sense of how much time it actually takes to keep on top of alongside the work. either way you'll know where you stand. does that work?</div></div>
  <div class="ibox" style="margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><p style="font-size:12px;"><strong>Why 2 weeks:</strong> long enough for them to either do it — great — or realise they are not going to. Most won't. When you call back they have sat with the gap long enough to feel it. Don't frame the follow-up as a chase. Frame it as a check-in after they've had a go themselves. The pain of not doing it does the work for you.</p></div>
  <div class="sb2"><div class="sl">If No / Not now</div><button class="cp" onclick="cpScr(this)">Copy</button>
  <div class="st">No problem at all. I will send the summary over — the action list is yours to use whether we work together or not. Good luck with it.</div></div>
  <div class="ibox" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap;"><div><p style="margin:0;">Immediately after the call — generate and send within 30 minutes. Every lead gets a send-out, yes or no.</p></div><button onclick="showSec('sendout',document.querySelector('[onclick*=sendout]'))" style="background:var(--blue);color:#fff;border:none;padding:9px 18px;border-radius:8px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer;font-family:var(--fh);white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">&#9993; Open Send-Out &rarr;</button></div>
</div>
</div>
</div><!-- /oncall -->

<!-- ─── CANCELLATION & RETENTION ─── -->
<div id="sc-cancel" class="tp">
<div class="card">
  <div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128683;</div><div><div class="ct">Cancellation &amp; Retention Scripts</div><div class="cs">When a client wants to leave — how to handle it and what to say</div></div></div>
  <div class="ibox"><p><strong>First rule:</strong> never react to the word "cancel" by processing a cancellation. The word "cancel" is almost always an expression of frustration, not a committed decision. Your job is to find out what's underneath it before you do anything else.</p></div>

  <div class="csec">Step 1 — The Opening Response (say this every time)</div>
  <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:10px;padding:18px 20px;font-size:13.5px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.9;margin-bottom:6px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">Of course — before I do anything, can I ask what's prompted this?</div>
  <div class="ibox"><p>Then stop talking. Let them answer. Do not defend, explain, or offer a discount. Just listen to what they say. The real reason will come out in the next 30 seconds.</p></div>

  <div class="csec">Step 2 — Identify Which of These Three Situations You're In</div>
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;margin-bottom:18px;">

    <div class="acc"><div class="acc-h" onclick="togAcc(this)">Situation A — "It's not working / I'm not seeing results" <span class="acc-arr">&#9660;</span></div>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p><strong>What's really happening:</strong> They don't know the results are there. This is a communication failure, not a delivery failure.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>What to say:</strong></p>
      <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.8;margin-top:8px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">I completely understand — let me pull up your numbers right now. When you started with us in [month] your profile had [X] reviews and was getting around [X] views a month. Right now you're at [X] reviews and [X] views. That's [X] more people finding you every month who weren't before.

The phone calls and enquiries are harder to track on your end — but those view numbers mean people are searching for your trade in [location] and landing on your profile. Can I ask — have you noticed any increase in calls or enquiries over the last couple of months?</div>
      <div class="acc-note">Pull their real numbers from the Clients sheet before this conversation. "Let me pull them up" is not a bluff — you should actually have them in front of you.</div>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>If they say they still haven't seen results:</strong></p>
      <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.8;margin-top:8px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">That's fair — and I want to make sure we fix that. Can we book a 15-minute call this week so I can go through the profile with you, show you exactly what's happening, and make sure we're pushing it in the right direction? If after that you still want to cancel, I'll sort it immediately — no argument.</div>
      <div class="acc-note">This call almost always saves the client. Seeing the dashboard together, in real time, makes the results undeniable.</div>
    </div></div>

    <div class="acc"><div class="acc-h" onclick="togAcc(this)">Situation B — "It's the money / cash flow is tight" <span class="acc-arr">&#9660;</span></div>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p><strong>What's really happening:</strong> A genuine financial pressure. Don't challenge it. Work with it.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>What to say:</strong></p>
      <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.8;margin-top:8px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">I hear you — and I'd rather work something out than lose you. What if we paused for one month rather than cancelled completely? Your profile stays live, nothing gets undone, and you pick it back up when things ease. No penalty, no awkwardness. Would that help?</div>
      <div class="acc-note">A pause costs you one month of £147. A cancellation costs you the client, the recurring revenue, and the relationship. A pause is almost always the right offer.</div>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>If they need to cancel regardless:</strong></p>
      <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.8;margin-top:8px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">No problem at all — I'll sort that for you now. And when things pick back up, just come back to us. Everything we've built is still there on Google, so you won't be starting from zero. Good luck with it — genuinely.</div>
      <div class="acc-note">Clean exits build goodwill. They will remember how you handled this. Several will come back.</div>
    </div></div>

    <div class="acc"><div class="acc-h" onclick="togAcc(this)">Situation C — "I've been approached by someone else / found a cheaper option" <span class="acc-arr">&#9660;</span></div>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p><strong>What's really happening:</strong> Someone has got in their ear and offered a lower price or made a bold claim. Do not panic and do not match the price.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>What to say:</strong></p>
      <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.8;margin-top:8px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">Can I ask who it is and what they're offering? I ask because there are a lot of people in this space making big promises and not delivering — and you've already been burned once before. I'm not saying don't go with them. I'm saying make sure you ask them: are they Gas Safe aware? Do they understand trades businesses specifically? What does their monthly reporting look like? And what happens to everything we've built when you switch?

Whatever you decide, the profile stays. But I'd hate for you to undo six months of work on a cheaper promise.</div>
      <div class="acc-note">You're not being defensive — you're being protective of their investment. That's the right frame. If they still leave, let them go cleanly.</div>
    </div></div>

  </div>

  <div class="csec">If They Confirm They Want to Cancel — The Clean Exit</div>
  <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:10px;padding:18px 20px;font-size:13.5px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.9;margin-bottom:12px;font-family:monospace;white-space:pre-wrap;">No problem at all — I'll cancel the payment now. Everything we've set up on your Google profile stays exactly as it is, so you keep all the reviews, the photos, the ranking work — none of that disappears.

If you ever want to pick it back up just drop me a message. And if anyone asks who sorted your Google presence, I'd really appreciate a mention. Good luck with it.</div>

  <div class="gbox"><strong>Log it in the CRM.</strong> Mark the lead as Churned and add a note for why. After five cancellations, look for the pattern. If clients are leaving at month 3, that's a delivery problem. If it's always "too expensive", that's a value communication problem. The data tells you what to fix.</div>

  <div class="csec">What Not to Do</div>
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px;">
    <div style="background:#fef2f2;border-radius:9px;padding:14px;"><div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--rd);margin-bottom:6px;">&#10007; Never do this</div><ul style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);line-height:2;padding-left:16px;"><li>Immediately process the cancel without asking why</li><li>Offer a discount to keep them</li><li>Get defensive about the work done</li><li>Guilt trip or pressure them</li><li>Argue about results</li></ul></div>
    <div style="background:#f0fdf4;border-radius:9px;padding:14px;"><div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gr);margin-bottom:6px;">&#10003; Always do this</div><ul style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);line-height:2;padding-left:16px;"><li>Ask why before reacting</li><li>Have their numbers ready</li><li>Offer a pause before a cancel</li><li>Exit cleanly if they insist</li><li>Log the reason in CRM</li></ul></div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>

</div><!-- /scripts -->

