  <div class="ibox"><p>Reports go out on the <strong>last Friday of every month</strong> to every managed client. After you send each one, call <code style="background:var(--grey);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:12px;">markReportSent("Client Name")</code> in your Google Apps Script to log it and schedule the next one. The Report Schedule tab in your sheet turns red automatically when a report is overdue.</p></div>

  <div class="csec">Adding a New Client to the Schedule</div>
  <div style="background:var(--nm);border-radius:10px;padding:14px 18px;font-family:monospace;font-size:12.5px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:14px;">addToReportSchedule("Smith Plumbing", "Tier 3 — Established", "dave@smithplumbing.co.uk")</div>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:18px;">Call this in Apps Script when you onboard a new managed client (T1, T3, or T4). It adds a row to the Report Schedule sheet and drops a calendar event on the last Friday of their first full month.</p>

  <div class="csec">After You Send a Report</div>
