  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:18px;">Call this in Apps Script after sending. It logs the date, advances the month counter, deletes the old calendar event, and creates the next one automatically. The row stays green.</p>

  <div class="csec">Monday Morning Check</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:14px 16px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);line-height:1.8;">Every Monday at 9am the script auto-checks for overdue reports and turns any late row red. Open the sheet, look for red rows, send those reports first before anything else that day. A overdue report is a client who doesn&#39;t know their results are working — those clients cancel.</div>
