<!-- ═══ GMB SETUP SOP ═══ -->
<div id="clt-gmb" class="tp">
<div class="card">
  <div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#128205;</div><div><div class="ct">GMB Setup SOP</div><div class="cs">How to build a Google Business Profile correctly — field by field</div></div></div>
  <div class="ibox"><p>A properly built GMB is the difference between ranking and not ranking. Every field below is there for a reason. Do not skip any of them. A half-built profile actively hurts ranking — Google penalises incomplete listings.</p></div>

  <div class="csec">Before You Start</div>
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="background:#fef2f2;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 14px;border-left:3px solid var(--rd);font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Required access:</strong> The client adds you as a Manager at business.google.com/manage. They go to Users → Add User → enter your Google email → set as Manager. Do NOT ask them to give you Owner access — Manager is sufficient and safer for the client. Confirm you can see the profile in your Google account before starting.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 1 — Basic Information</div>
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Business Name</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">Exact legal trading name. No keyword stuffing (e.g. "Dave's Plumbing Manchester Emergency" is against Google's rules and will get the profile suspended). Just the real name.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Primary Category</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">The most important field. Use the most specific category available. Search in GMB: "Plumber" not "Contractor". "Electrician" not "Home Services". Google uses this to decide what searches to show you for. Get it wrong and nothing else matters.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Secondary Categories</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">Add up to 9 more. A plumber should add: "Heating Contractor", "Boiler Repair Service", "Bathroom Remodeler", "Gas Installation Service". Each category is an additional search term you can rank for.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Phone Number</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">The number they want to receive calls on. Mobile is fine. Must be live and answered — Google tests it and uses call data as a ranking signal.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Website</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">Add the website URL once built. If no website yet, leave blank — do not add a Facebook page or other social link here.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Address or Service Area</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">If they have a fixed address (office, depot), add it. If they work from home and don't want the address shown, use Service Area instead — add every town and postcode district they cover. Do both if possible. More coverage = more ranking opportunities.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:12px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--grey);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--gm);">
      <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Opening Hours</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tx);">Set accurate hours. If they do emergency call-outs outside hours, that's fine — the hours are for the office/standard availability. Add a special hours note if needed. Profiles with accurate hours rank better than those showing "hours not available".</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 2 — Business Description (750 characters — use every one)</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:16px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:10px;">This is the most important text field on the profile. Google reads it for keywords. Write it in this order:</div>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;">
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Sentence 1:</strong> Who they are + trade + location. "Smith Plumbing &amp; Heating are a fully qualified Gas Safe registered plumber based in Manchester."</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Sentences 2–4:</strong> Their main services, each mentioned by name. Include the city/town again naturally. "We specialise in boiler installation, boiler repair and servicing, and central heating installation across Manchester and surrounding areas including Salford, Stretford, and Didsbury."</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Sentence 5:</strong> Accreditation or trust signal. "Gas Safe registered (No. 123456), fully insured, all work guaranteed for 12 months."</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Sentence 6:</strong> CTA. "Call now for a free no-obligation quote or emergency call-out — available 7 days a week."</div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:10px;background:#fef3c7;border-radius:7px;padding:10px;font-size:12px;color:#78350f;"><strong>Important:</strong> Do not use ALL CAPS, hashtags, URLs, or promotional language like "best" or "#1" — Google will suppress or reject the description.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 3 — Services</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:8px;">In the GMB dashboard, go to Edit Profile → Services. Add every service they offer as a separate item. Each service can have a name and a short description. Use the same service names as the website. Google uses these to match you to specific search queries.</div>
    <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--tl);">A plumber should have: Boiler Installation, Boiler Repair, Boiler Servicing, Central Heating Installation, Bathroom Fitting, Emergency Plumbing, Leak Detection, Gas Safety Certificates, Unvented Cylinder Installation. Each as a separate line.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 4 — Photos (This is where most profiles fall short)</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;">
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Logo:</strong> Upload their logo PNG. This shows on the profile card in search results. Must be clear at small size.</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Cover photo:</strong> Best completed job or team photo. Landscape format. This is the first thing someone sees when they click on the profile.</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Work photos (minimum 5, aim for 10+):</strong> Real photos of completed jobs. Label each one with a description when uploading — "Boiler installation Manchester" not "IMG_4823". Google reads photo filenames and descriptions.</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--fh);">Team or van photo:</strong> One photo of the person or their van. This dramatically increases trust — people want to know who's coming to their home.</div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:10px;background:#fef3c7;border-radius:7px;padding:10px;font-size:12px;color:#78350f;"><strong>Never use stock photos.</strong> Google detects them and they reduce trust signals. All photos must be real. Even a slightly blurry real photo beats a perfect stock image.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 5 — Attributes</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;">In Edit Profile → More, there are attributes specific to the business type. Tick every one that's true: "Identifies as women-owned", "LGBTQ+ friendly", "Online estimates", "On-site services", "Language assistance" if applicable. These appear on the profile and can influence which searches surface the listing.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 6 — Q&amp;A Section</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:8px;">The Q&amp;A section on GMB allows anyone to ask and answer questions. Seed it yourself with the 3–5 questions clients actually ask:</div>
    <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--tl);">
      Q: Are you Gas Safe registered? A: Yes, Gas Safe registration number [XXXXX].<br>
      Q: Do you cover [nearby town]? A: Yes, we cover [town list].<br>
      Q: Do you do emergency call-outs? A: Yes, available 7 days a week.<br>
      Q: How quickly can you respond? A: Same day for most jobs, within 2 hours for emergencies.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="csec">Step 7 — First Post</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:4px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;">Publish the first GMB post before considering the setup complete. Use the Post Factory in this hub. A profile with a recent post is seen as active by Google and ranks higher than an otherwise identical profile with no posts. The post should include: a photo, the service name, the location, and a call to action.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="gbox" style="margin-top:14px;"><strong>Setup is complete when:</strong> All 7 steps done, the profile shows 100% completion in the GMB dashboard, there is at least one photo in every category, at least one post is live, and the website URL is linked.</div>
</div>
</div>

