<div id="wb2-copy" class="tp">
<div class="card">
  <div class="ch"><div class="ci">&#9999;</div><div><div class="ct">Copy Guide</div><div class="cs">What Google reads — get this right and the site ranks</div></div></div>
  <div class="ibox"><p>The prompt generator writes most of this for you. This guide explains why each piece matters so you can check the output and improve it if needed.</p></div>
  <div class="csec">Page Title (Yoast) &mdash; Most Important SEO Element</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:16px;margin-bottom:14px;">
    <div style="font-family:var(--fh);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;">Format: [Trade] in [Location] | [Business Name]</div>
    <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:8px;">Max 60 characters. Google cuts anything longer.</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong>Good:</strong> "Plumber in Manchester | Smith Plumbing &amp; Heating"</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;margin-top:4px;"><strong>Good:</strong> "Emergency Electrician Sheffield | JD Electrical Services"</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--rd);margin-top:8px;"><strong>Bad:</strong> "Welcome to Smith Plumbing" &mdash; Google can't tell what you do or where</div>
  </div>
  <div class="csec">Hero H1 Headline</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:16px;margin-bottom:14px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:6px;">Trade + Location must be in the H1. Google uses this to understand what the page is about. The prompt generator writes this automatically.</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;"><strong>Good:</strong> "Your Local Plumber in Manchester"</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--rd);margin-top:6px;"><strong>Bad:</strong> "Quality Services For All Your Needs" &mdash; meaningless to Google and to people</div>
  </div>
  <div class="csec">Services &mdash; How to Write Each One</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:16px;margin-bottom:14px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:8px;">Each service card: specific name (not "general plumbing" &mdash; "Boiler Installation &amp; Servicing"), 2&ndash;3 sentences with what's included and what the client is known for.</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--gr);"><strong>&#10003; Good:</strong> "Boiler Installation &amp; Servicing — We supply and install all major brands including Worcester Bosch and Ideal. All installations include a full system flush and 12-month labour guarantee."</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--rd);margin-top:6px;"><strong>&#10007; Weak:</strong> "We offer boiler services including installation and repair." &mdash; Not enough for Google or for the customer.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="csec">About Section Interview Questions</div>
  <div style="background:var(--grey);border-radius:9px;padding:16px;margin-bottom:14px;">
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:4px;">How long have you been doing this trade?</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:4px;">Did you work for someone else before going out on your own?</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:4px;">Why did you decide to go out on your own?</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);margin-bottom:4px;">What makes you different from a bigger company?</div>
    <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tl);">What areas do you cover and how far will you travel?</div>
  </div>
  <div class="wbox"><strong>The golden rule:</strong> Trade + location should appear in the H1, the page title, the meta description, the services copy, and the about section. That repetition is intentional &mdash; Google needs to see it multiple times to understand what the page is about.</div>
</div>
</div>

