<div id="pf-guide" class="tp">
<div class="g2">
<div>
<div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-icon">📋</div><div><div class="card-title">CSV Format</div><div class="card-sub">How to structure your content file</div></div></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:12px;">Your CSV needs at minimum two columns:</p>
<div style="background:var(--navy);border-radius:9px;padding:16px;font-family:monospace;font-size:12px;color:#cdd5e0;line-height:2;">
<span style="color:#45b3f5;">Headline</span>,<span style="color:#45b3f5;">Body_Text</span>,<span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.4);">Category</span><br>
"New boiler fitted in Manchester","Installed a Viessmann 100W...","Boiler"<br>
"Emergency callout — leak fixed same day","Mr Johnson called at 7am...","Emergency"
</div>
<p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--tl);">Category is optional but groups posts visually. Body_Text becomes the bullet points — write 2–4 sentences or use line breaks for multiple bullets.</p>
</div>

<div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-icon">📸</div><div><div class="card-title">Getting the Best from Photos</div><div class="card-sub">What makes a great GMB post image</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">1</div><div><div class="stit">Before and after shots</div><div class="sdesc">Show the transformation. Trades that post before/after photos consistently get 40%+ more profile views.</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">2</div><div><div class="stit">Job completion photos</div><div class="sdesc">The finished installation, the clean site, the happy customer (with permission). Real beats stock every time.</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">3</div><div><div class="stit">Van or team photos</div><div class="sdesc">People hire people. A photo of the team or the branded van builds immediate trust.</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">4</div><div><div class="stit">If you have nothing — use colour</div><div class="sdesc">The Dark, Blue, and Amber themes produce professional-looking posts with no photo needed. That's the safety net.</div></div></div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-icon">🗓</div><div><div class="card-title">How to Use the Posts</div><div class="card-sub">Getting them live on GMB</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">1</div><div><div class="stit">Download the ZIP</div><div class="sdesc">All posts download as 1080×1080 PNG images, ready to upload directly to Google Business Profile.</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">2</div><div><div class="stit">Open Google Business Profile</div><div class="sdesc">Go to business.google.com → Posts → Add Update → Upload image → Paste the Body_Text as the caption.</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">3</div><div><div class="stit">Schedule one per week minimum</div><div class="sdesc">Weekly posting is a GMB ranking signal. Monthly is the minimum. Daily is ideal if you have the content.</div></div></div>
<div class="sstep"><div class="sn">4</div><div><div class="stit">Mix real jobs with evergreen content</div><div class="sdesc">Generate evergreen seasonal posts using this tool. Use real job posts when the client sends photos. Both matter.</div></div></div>
</div>
<div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-icon">🛡</div><div><div class="card-title">Why This Protects the Client</div></div></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;">Google's local ranking algorithm rewards active profiles. A business that stops posting:</p>
<div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--rd);">↓</span><span>Loses position in the local pack gradually</span></div>
